From eb2bd048ae2f96ecb80c79bf780341556210b963 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Mr. Figueredo" <311303@dadeschools.net>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 15:35:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Add Solver, Distractor Engine, and Prompt Renderer
 support for advanced circle angles and geometric mean
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Completes the full 5-stage pipeline for the 4 new templates added in
the previous commit: two-chords interior circle angle, exterior
secant/tangent circle angle, tangent-chord angle, and the right
triangle altitude geometric mean.

Solver (v1.9.0 -> v1.10.0): all four templates return a pre-computed
exact value from the generator.

Distractor Engine (v1.9.0 -> v1.10.0), each grounded in a real error:
- circle_angle_two_chords: the single highest-value distractor is the
  EXTERIOR-angle formula (half the difference instead of half the
  sum) — confusing the two-chords-inside theorem with the
  secants-outside theorem is the most common real error for this
  topic, since both are 'half of something involving two arcs.' Also:
  forgetting to halve, and using only one arc.
- circle_angle_exterior: the companion confusion — using the
  INTERIOR-angle formula (half the sum instead of half the
  difference), plus forgetting to halve and using only the far arc.
- tangent_chord_angle: forgetting to halve, confusing the intercepted
  arc with its major-arc complement (360 - arc) before halving, and
  doubling instead of halving.
- right_triangle_altitude_geometric_mean: averaging the two segments
  instead of taking the geometric mean (a common real confusion
  between arithmetic and geometric mean), multiplying without the
  square root, and simply adding the segments.

Prompt Renderer (v1.9.0 -> v1.10.0): fully-specified text-only
questions for all four templates.

Verification:
- 4 new templates x 40 seeds = 160 runs through the full 5-stage
  pipeline, 0 failures.
- Re-ran at 100 seeds x 4 templates (400 runs), 0 failures.
- Full regression: all 61 certified templates (57 previous + 4 new)
  re-verified through the complete 5-stage pipeline, 61/61 pass.
- Composed and printed a full 61-question quiz using every single
  certified template exactly once (no repeats), confirming the Quiz
  Composer and Quiz Printer both scale correctly to the full current
  template set, not just small samples.

This closes the interior/exterior/tangent-chord circle angle gaps
(Chapter 10.5) and the similar-right-triangles geometric mean gap
(Chapter 9.3), bringing the certified pipeline to 61 templates.
